# Only admins may approve changes to scored results, leaderboards, the global
# index, generated JSON schemas, the runner package and CI workflows.
#
# CODEOWNERS only enforces review on PRs — it does NOT protect main from
# direct pushes. Enable branch protection in Settings → Branches to also
# require PRs and passing CI before merging.
#
# See https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-security/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# Score results are the main audit trail — humans review these.
tasks/*/results/        @yupesh

# Runner package, schemas, and CI/workflow definitions stay human-reviewed.
/schemas/               @yupesh
/.github/               @yupesh
/runner/                @yupesh

# NOTE: `/data/` and `**/leaderboard.json` are generated by the `aggregate`
# workflow on pushes to main and committed by `github-actions[bot]`. Owning
# them with @yupesh would either (a) block the bot's direct push via required
# review, or (b) be vacuous (CODEOWNERS doesn't apply to direct pushes to
# main anyway). Either way, humans should never hand-edit these.
